## Frequency and PITR constraints

The provider validates the following at plan time before any task is dispatched. Failing any
of these returns a plan-time error.

- `frequency` must be at least `1h`. Sub-hourly schedules are rejected.
- `incremental_backup_frequency` must be at most `24h`.
- `enable_point_in_time_restore = true` requires `incremental_backup_frequency` to be set.
- Adding `incremental_backup_frequency` to an existing schedule forces resource recreation
  (YBA does not support enabling incremental backups on an existing schedule in place).
- Removing `incremental_backup_frequency` from an existing schedule is rejected; incremental
  backups cannot be disabled once enabled.

